<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6158&amp;p=58109#p58109"><![CDATA[
I just have recevied my Super Power Pak and it's really great, altough I have the following request for a future PowerPak update :<br /><br />- Move everything one tile right on the menu... I can only see a part of the cursor on the bottom of the screen and see nothing on the top of the screen on my TV, because the leftmost pixels are clipped and this is very annoying I have to "guess" where the cursor is, by entering into folders, which is kinda terrible<br /><br />- The Super Power Pak can't run 256kb ROMs. I had to extend programs I made to 512kb to test them on the real Hardware<br /><br />- There is a good auto-save feature, but when running a ROM with SRAM you have to do trough a long and complex procedure to load a .srm file, it goes to root and you have to select the folder again, etc.. (without seeing the cursor)<br /><br />- I had to reformat the cart to FAT32 to not get an error<br /><br />- The incremental scrolling cursor is very annoying. I with it'd scroll one entry at a time<br /><br />- .spc file without using another program would be awesome<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sat Mar 13, 2010 4:47 am</p><hr />
